Collection/UserLabel retirement restoration snippets (Android)
===============================================================

These snippets preserve the removed mixed-file public/UI surface. The four
dedicated source files are archived separately under files/app/ with their
original relative paths.

UrlSaverRoot.kt (removed public/UI surface)
-------------------------------------------
- MainScreen callbacks: onCollectionDeleted, onCollectionDeleteFailed
- Main/Archive collection state: collections, selectedCollectionIdFlow,
  customCollections, collection-name filtering, collection selection effects
- ManualInputSheet collection target fields and CollectionFilterRow block
- createCollectionState, pendingDeleteCollection, CreateCollectionDialog,
  confirmCreateCollection, reorderCollections, toggleSelectedCollection,
  deleteCollection, and collection assignment callbacks
- DetailScreen currentCollection, availableCollectionTags,
  locallyRemovedCollectionIds, DetailTagItem.Collection, and collection
  assign/clear branches
- filterEntriesBySearch collection parameter and collection-name predicate

ServiceFilterRow.kt (removed collection filter model)
-------------------------------------------------------
- TopFilterItem.Collection and collectionId token handling
- resolvedTopFilterTokens/buildMovableItems collection parameters and items
- collection selection/create/reorder callbacks and chips

The active source keeps Room compatibility entities/DAOs and legacy
collectionId/userLabelId storage; these snippets are UI/API-only removal
material and are intentionally not applied to database migrations.
